#!/usr/bin/env lowfat-filter
# rsync-compact — compact rsync output for LLM contexts.
# env: $sub $level $exit $args
#
# `rsync -v` lists every transferred file, then prints the stats block
# (`sent … received … bytes/sec`, `total size … speedup …`) at the END. The
# stats are the signal (did it work, how much moved); the file list is the
# bloat. ultra tails to the stats (+ last files); errors pass raw.

*:
    if exit failed:
        raw
    else:
        match level:
            ultra: tail 15
            lite:  tail 200
            else:  tail 50
